 "description": "Giants throw like mobile light catapults to a 20-foot... rather, per the source, a 20' range, and their huge weapons deal two dice of damage. A wandering Giant carries 1,000-6,000 Gold Pieces in his shoulder sack. Types: Hill (HD 8, cave lair, 12' tall, 60% of encounters); Stone (9, cave, 15', throws as a heavy catapult); Frost (10+1, castle, 18', impervious to cold, 2 dice +1 damage); Fire (11+3, castle, 12', impervious to fire, 2 dice +2 damage); Cloud (12+2, castle, 20', keen scent, 3 dice damage) — the last four 10% each. Castle-dwelling Giants have a 50% chance of monstrous guards: d6 1-4 a Hydra of 5-10 heads, 5-6 either 6-36 wolves or 3-18 bears.",
